cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and classification tasks, which are typically covered under the arXiv sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of pre-trained language models and their fine-tuning for classification tasks also falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The comparison of different classification models and their performance evaluation can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
